## Module Architecture at a Glance

```
Presentation Layer
├── app (Main entry point, wires features)
├── feature:dashboard
├── feature:searchfriend
├── feature:myfriends
├── feature:myprofile
├── feature:posttransaction
├── feature:billing
└── coreui (Shared components, theme, navigators)

Domain Layer
└── shared:domain (Repository interfaces, entities; path `shared/domain/`)

Data Access Layer
├── shared:data (KMP — repository implementations, DataStore interfaces)
├── shared:api (KMP — remote clients, DTOs, e.g. Ktor)
└── shared:database (KMP — Room, DataStore implementations)

Cross-Cutting Concerns
├── shared:tracking (KMP — `TrackingRepository` impl + Koin `trackingModule`)
├── shared:di (KMP — Koin `apiModule` / `dataModule` in `commonMain`)
└── app (`startKoin`, `DatabaseModule`, feature Koin modules)
```

---

## Golden Rule: Dependency Direction

**Presentation → Domain → Data**

```
Features (app, feature:*)
    ↓ depends on ↓
domain (interfaces only)
    ↓ depends on ↓
:shared:data, :shared:api, :shared:database (implementations)
```

**Never violate this:**
- ❌ Feature modules never import from `:shared:data`, `:shared:api`, or `database` implementation code
- ❌ ViewModel never directly instantiates repository implementations
- ✅ All dependencies resolved through Koin DI container

