## State Management Pattern

Every screen follows this state management flow:

```
User Action
    ↓
ViewModel.onAction()
    ↓
Repository.operation()
    ↓
_uiState.update { newState }  ← Single source of truth
    ↓
Screen collects uiState
    ↓
View renders new state
```

### State must be:
- **Immutable** (use `data class`, `sealed class`, `PersistentList`)
- **Complete** (all data needed to render is in the state)
- **Predictable** (same input always produces same state)
- **Single source** (one StateFlow per screen, not multiple)

